analysis.summary: This 2016 news article reports on a court hearing where government prosecutors argued that two of Jeffrey Epstein's victims should not be considered victims under federal law because they were allegedly complicit in procuring other girls. The victims' attorney expressed surprise and disappointment at this new argument being raised eight years after the original case.
